{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782085885571,"sessionID":"ses_1137165f2ffe96g8gg0Q3zOCJg","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_fd888aa45727430fa3b752df","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/benchmark-runs/cheap-arm/workspaces/h3c3-f580b748/README.md","content":"# Temperature Conversion Package\n\nA simple Python package for converting temperatures between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin.\n\n## Installation\nInstall the package using pip:\n\n```bash\npip install .\n```\n\nOr, if you're developing locally:\n\n```bash\npip install -e .\n```\n\n## CLI Usage\nConvert temperature values using the command-line interface:\n\n```bash\npython cli.py 25 --to-fahrenheit\npython cli.py 32 --to-kelvin\n```\n\n## Testing\nRun the tests using Python's unittest module:\n\n```bash\npython -m unittest test_converters.py\npython -m unittest test_cli.py\n```"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/benchmark-runs/cheap-arm/workspaces/h3c3-f580b748/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"benchmark-runs/cheap-arm/workspaces/h3c3-f580b748/README.md","time":{"start":1782085885559,"end":1782085885567}},"id":"prt_eec989e6e0013eb9bzOFOQzQ1c","sessionID":"ses_1137165f2ffe96g8gg0Q3zOCJg","messageID":"msg_eec976f2d001ofS7GWH1LGDiII"}}
